Honestly the story of Saint Drogo is so bizarre... Seemingly random bilocation (working in field and being in church for Mass), somehow on a piligrimage changing visually and becoming so monstrous they had to lock him away from people... What the hell? There is so much going on..

They built his dark cell next to the church.. They knew he was a holy man and yet he looked so monstrous they could not look at him.. Back then people werent pretty at all, how horrifying must he have been? To know him a saint and not to look at him.. Are we talkn Lovecraft tier?

And somehow he is a saint of coffee? @MaansnijderJan associated this with Sufism, someone else pointed bilocation is also common for Sufi saints... Honestly his tale seems very uncharacteristic for Christianity I feel, something very unusual in it, and yet he is a catholic saint
